A general view of the outside of a COVID-19 ward at  Hospital in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa has recorded 2,782 new COVID-19 cases in the past 24 hours. 916 of those were identified in Gauteng with 467 in the Western Cape and 352 in KwaZulu Natal. READ: COVID-19 in SA | Fifth wave expected before winter All other provinces recorded less than 300 new cases. Sadly, a further 14 people have died.  #COVID19 UPDATE: 31,110 tests were conducted in the last 24hrs, with 2,782 new cases, representing an 8.9% positivity rate. Today, @HealthZA reports 221 deaths, of which 14 occurred in the past 24-48 hours. Total fatalities are 95,766 to date. More here: https://t.co/ymEuX8vDUC pic.twitter.com/Ggy6iAs5Hj